TITLE: Russia scrambles to repair Crimea bridge, Zelenskyy vows to accelerate 'victory'
SUMMARY: Russia is scrambling to repair Kerch Bridge by July 1, 2023, after explosions severely damaged President Vladimir Putin's prized Crimean bridge over the weekend.

TITLE: Anti-oil environmentalists pour tomato soup on Van Gogh 'Sunflowers' painting
SUMMARY: A climate activist duo with the climate change group Just Stop Oil threw cans of tomato soup on a piece of artwork by Vincent van Gogh in a central London museum.

TITLE: Brazil had 'love' with Trump, 'indifference' with Biden, economy minister says
SUMMARY: Brazil's economics minister argued the U.S. regularly makes trade deals with countries like Venezuela and China, then criticizes other nations for doing the same.

TITLE: Russia's Wagner group makes 'some' advances in Donbas in first tactical gains since July: UK intel
SUMMARY: The Kremlin-linked Wagner mercenary group has helped Russia make some advances in the fiercely contested Donbas region in Ukraine.

TITLE: North Korea fires missile, artillery shells, inflaming tensions
SUMMARY: North Korea is stirring fears of war as the country conducts ballistic missile launches and fires hundreds of artillery shells toward the sea.

TITLE: Biden drove 'historically' close Middle East allies into the arms of America's greatest enemies, experts say
SUMMARY: Experts are warning that Biden has hurt longstanding security partnerships in the Middle East and risked moving countries closer to adversaries such as China and Russia.

TITLE: UN watchdog accuses top human rights official of 'harassment, censorship and discrimination'
SUMMARY: The United Nations Human Rights Council said it chose speakers using an unbiased algorithm, but a whistleblower claims the council's top official openly berated the group.

TITLE: Iraqi lawmakers elect new president hours after rockets fall near parliament building
SUMMARY: Iraqi officials have elected a new president, former minister Abdul Latif Rashid, only hours after nine rockets landed near the nation's parliament building.

TITLE: Putin doubles down on proposal to make Turkey energy hub
SUMMARY: Russian President Vladimir Putin has once again proposed turning Turkey into a gas hub for Europe after gas delivery to Germany was halted by the Baltic Sea pipeline disaster.

TITLE: Germany plans to introduce global public transit pass
SUMMARY: Germany is planning to introduce a public transit pass that would cost $47 a month and be used anywhere around the world. German officials are currently trying to figure out funding.
